      "content": "Yes, I can certainly help you plan a quick 3-day trip to Singapore, though I must warn you that the trip will be very busy and you will need to be very careful with your schedule.\n\nFor your meetings in Jurong East, you should take the MRT to Jurong East Station, which is a direct stop on the North-South Line and East-West Line, but you will need to be very early to avoid the crowds and the \"Jurong East Express\" that sometimes delays trains.\n\nFor a formal business dinner, I recommend dining at **Café de l'Homme** or **Monsieur Paris** in Marina Bay, as they offer excellent views and a professional atmosphere, though you will need to book well in advance. Alternatively, try **Gaggan Anand** for a unique culinary experience, but be aware that the wait times can be long and the service style is very fast-paced.\n\nRegarding your logistics, the MRT system is efficient, but you must be mindful of the \"Jurong East Express\" which can cause significant delays, so always check the station announcements before leaving your office. If you miss your train, you may need to take the bus to the next station, which can be",
